{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require coriander be displayed in bold text in all product ingredient lists",
        "additional_details": "There are some individuals who may have allergies or may have sensitivities to coriander.\r\n\r\nSome previous scientific research has suggested the genes OR10A6 and OR10A are partially responsible for a strong like or dislike of fresh coriander giving consumers the unfortunate flavour of \"soap\" from the herb.\r\n\r\nCoriander is a common ingredient, yet not all consumers may be aware of its presence. I believe by making it bold, we can help ensure that those who need to avoid it can easily identify it. ",
        "background": "Require that all products containing coriander display it in bold text to help consumers avoid purchasing and wasting products.",
